@jimj you can use the web console data loader to make the JSON for you:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/177816/69365948-31276500-0c4a-11ea-914e-aa6de33bdf5b.png)

In the final step (where you can submit the spec) you can also copy out the JSON. You can treat the data loader as a very very fancy JSON spec editor.

`tsv` is actually for delimited file formats and its default separator is a tab. But you should be able to set a custom delimiter by adding a `delimiter` parameter as below.

```json
        "parseSpec" : {
          "format" : "tsv",
          "delimiter": "|",
          "timestampSpec" : {
            "column": "l_shipdate",
            "format": "yyyy-MM-dd"
          },
```
